    <h2>What Is Speechify?</h2>
    <p>Speechify is an AI-powered text-to-speech (TTS) platform that converts any text into natural-sounding audio. Whether it's a blog post, PDF, book, or document, Speechify can read it aloud with realistic AI voices.</p>
    <p>Founded in 2016, Speechify has grown to over <strong>20 million users</strong> and offers the most natural-sounding AI voices in the industry. It's used by students, professionals, content creators, and people with reading difficulties.</p>

    <h2>Our Testing Process</h2>
    <p>We used Speechify for 2 full weeks on real projects:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>5 audiobook conversions (public domain books)</li>
      <li>20 article-to-audio conversions (blog posts, news articles)</li>
      <li>10 PDF document readings</li>
      <li>5 YouTube video transcriptions and audio</li>
      <li>3 podcast episode voiceovers</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Every output was compared against <a href="/comparisons">other TTS tools</a> we've tested.</p>

    <h2>Key Features</h2>

    <h3>1. Natural-Sounding AI Voices</h3>
    <p>Speechify offers over 200 AI voices in 50+ languages. The premium voices (especially the "Natural" and "Studio" tiers) are incredibly realistic — we often couldn't tell they were AI-generated. The voices have proper intonation, pauses, and emotional depth.</p>

    <h3>2. Document & Web Import</h3>
    <p>You can import:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>PDF files (reads with OCR for scanned docs)</li>
      <li>Web articles (paste URL or use browser extension)</li>
      <li>Word documents (.docx)</li>
      <li>Plain text</li>
      <li>Images (via OCR)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The browser extension is particularly useful — click a button and any webpage becomes an audio experience.</p>

    <h3>3. Custom Voice Cloning</h3>
    <p>Speechify lets you clone your own voice or create a custom AI voice. Upload 3 minutes of audio and Speechify creates a digital twin that can read any text in your voice. This is great for content creators who want consistent voiceovers.</p>

    <h3>4. Audiobook Creation</h3>
    <p>You can convert any book or document into an audiobook. The playback interface includes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Adjustable speed (0.5x to 4x)</li>
      <li>Skip ahead/skip back by sentences or paragraphs</li>
      <li>Highlight text as it's read</li>
      <li>Chapter navigation</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. Mobile Apps</h3>
    <p>Speechify has iOS and Android apps for listening on the go. The apps sync with your web library, so you can start a book on your laptop and continue on your phone.</p>

