    <h2>Who Should Use Speechify?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Students</strong> who want to listen to textbooks and articles on the go</li>
      <li><strong>Content creators</strong> making audiobooks, podcasts, or YouTube voiceovers</li>
      <li><strong>Professionals</strong> who consume lots of articles and reports</li>
      <li><strong>People with reading difficulties</strong> (dyslexia, vision impairment)</li>
      <li><strong>Language learners</strong> who want to practice listening comprehension</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who Should Skip It?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Basic needs only</strong> — free built-in TTS in browsers may suffice</li>
      <li><strong>Voice actor careers</strong> — AI voices won't replace human voice actors yet</li>
      <li><strong>Tight budgets</strong> — alternatives like NaturalReader are cheaper</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our Verdict</h2>
    <p>Speechify is the <strong>best text-to-speech tool</strong> we've tested. The voice quality is unmatched — premium voices sound genuinely human with proper emotional intonation. The voice cloning feature is a game-changer for content creators who want consistent audio.</p>
    <p>It's not perfect (free plan is limited, and it can get expensive), but for anyone who consumes content in audio format — whether students, professionals, or content creators — Speechify delivers real value.</p>
    <p><strong>Our score: 8.8/10</strong></p>

